    "updated_at": "2016-06-09T16:49:27Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Emacs uses control-space to make a note of the beginning of the selection, but in classic Emacs (and I believe also readline) this does _not_ enter a special confusing mode. It just makes a note of where the cursor was when control-space was pressed (\"sets the mark\"), and carries on as normal.\n\nIn modern Emacs it does activate a somewhat special mode (\"active mark mode\"), but this doesn't interfere with normal editing -- it just causes the space between the cursor and the marked point to be highlighted.\n\nEither of these seems preferable to the special \"you can't do anything except select\" mode that I guess ipython is entering now?\n"
  },
